          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 55</h1><p><strong>Questions 21 - 26</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>21 One of the students is not at the meeting because ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... he is at home sick.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... he is at home doing some research.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... he has forgotten about the meeting.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>22 The first thing the students decide to do is ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... visit the larger sports facilities in the town.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... make the research question more specific.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... design a questionnaire.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>23 The group want to ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... compare the number of people with heart disease and strokes.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... discover how local people think sports facilities influence their health.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... better understand how healthy their town is.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>24 A comparison between the present and 30-35 years ago was chosen because ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... the group are interested in people of this age range.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... Rick can easily find this data on the internet.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... most of the sports facilities opened this long ago.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>25 They all agree to ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... only focus on physical health.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... focus on both physical and mental health.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>   